<br>
BTW the wizzy just TP everyone to bazaar for KEI every couple of hours.  On my server it goes for a 50 pp  donation.  The mages keep us in focus items. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1059<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/11/02 12:07 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: unconventional, yet effective, groups</span><hr size=1> Had a fun time with a 54 beastlord, a druid, and a bard in ME yesterday. Was going great taking out yellow mobs to 54. Until a damn bard repeatedly <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> attempted</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to swarm kite our area resulting in my death... twice. /sigh <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upilsainsilverback.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pilsain Silverback</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/11/02 12:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: unconventional, yet effective, groups</span><hr size=1> Lately, I prefer grouping with other wizards, druids, bards, and necro's/SK's.  Caster groups seem to be more dynamic, and safer than melee groups.<br>
