<br>
A group of hybrids with a bard can do extremely well.  All the hybrids have some form of health replacement, bard can do cc, mana, and health regen.  With a little bit of clever aggro management (spread it around) the bards health song is maximized.<br>
<br>
Bards are underutilized.  Buy your kei, then group with a bard.  :-).<br>
<br>
In the upper levels, necros provide mana replacement too, (and not just twitching).  For wizards and for clerics, mana === dps.  In the wizard's case, it's direct.  In the clerics case, mana =&gt; health =&gt; melee endurance.<br>
<br>
Awlin 52 wiz<br>
Aidal 57 cleric <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=finiel>Finiel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/20/02 5:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> I had some success when my enchanter was in his 30's partnering with a wizard and a paladin (sometimes a bard too). It was a lot of fun, we could handle situations I could only dream of taking on alone. The paladin could provide plenty of healing with clarity, and also could keep things attacking him instead of us. The wizard brought firepower, and the enchanter (and bard) did a little of everything. I usually used my animation rather than rely on charm with the small group. <br>
<br>
It did help that the others had similar ideas about the game that I do, and considered exploring dangerous situations to be the fun part of the game. The others stopped playing a while back. Now that Instrument of Nife and Lesser Evacuate  are in the game I get the urge for my wizard to try to gather up a few paladins and maybe an enchanter and go tear up an undead-heavy dungeon like Guk or City of Mist. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=metimbo2>metimbo2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/31/02 10:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I have had great success with a rogue partner.  Snare, flux till outta range, Biggest Nuke. That gets aggro on you for a while.  Rogue starts backstabbing while you are kiting.  Cast again when mob is down to like 1/4 health to keep aggro.  No one ever gets touched and is lots of fun ) <p>Metimbo Thewyze<br>
