V. We broke the biggest rule out there for PoV :p<br>
<br>
No Cleric! OMG<br>
<br>
Group line up was --- Wizard, Druid, War, Pally, chanter, Bard.<br>
<br>
The druid had no problem keeping up with heals, most people won't group with out a cleric --- personally if I can't find a cleric I go looking for a druid and it always seems to work - you lose some cleric buffs but thats not as much of a big deal as some people make out.<br>
<br>
We did however need a slower, though I've done these camps with the mobs at full speed and the cleric was able to keep up - I don't think a druid could.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, and the war was not the main tank - the pally was so we could get some sweet stun action going. War pulled. The bard didn't say much but did twist 3 or 4 songs constantly hehe.<br>
<br>
I hate all the set-groups that people seem they HAVE to form or they won't group. Sure theres optimal groups --- War, Cler, Shaman and 3 others with dps. but that's so damn boring.<br>
<br>
As far as I am concerned you need: (1) Plate Class - war/pal/sk, (1) Healer clr/dru, (1) slower bst/enc/sha {and yes bst 30% is good enough}, and any 3 others that can pump out some dps.<br>
<br>
Most people are sceptical when non-conventional groups form, then realise that there is more to grouping that the holy trinity. Hell I pull sometimes, and I'm good at it too.<br>
<br>
- Krynos <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izenblazeincindevesor>Izenblaze Incindevesor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 585<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/6/03 10:49 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard / Shaman</span><hr size=1> I love my guild cleric and paladin that I group with a lot.  The 3 of us is all we really need. <p><center><font color= red><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=351590>Izenblaze Incindevesor</a><BR>
